org.semanticweb.vlog4j.rdf

Class RdfModelConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.vlog4j.rdf.RdfModelConverter

  • public final class RdfModelConverter
extends Object
    Class for converting RDF Models to PositiveLiteral sets. Converts each <subject, predicate, object> triple statement of the given rdfModel into an PositiveLiteral of the form TRIPLE(subject, predicate, object). The ternary predicate used for all literals generated from RDF triples is RDF_TRIPLE_PREDICATE. Subject, predicate and object Values are converted to corresponding Terms:
    • URIs are converted to Constants with the escaped URI String as name.
    • Literals are converted to Constants with names containing the canonical form of the literal label, the data type and the language.
    • BNodes are converted to Blanks with the generated blank ID as name. BNodes have unique generated IDs in the context a Models. Blanks with the same name loaded from different models will have different ids.
    Author:
    Irina Dragoste

    • Method Detail

      • rdfModelToPositiveLiterals

        public static Set<PositiveLiteral> rdfModelToPositiveLiterals(org.openrdf.model.Model rdfModel)
        Converts each <subject, predicate, object> triple statement of the given rdfModel into a PositiveLiteral of the form TRIPLE(subject, predicate, object). See RDF_TRIPLE_PREDICATE, the ternary predicate used for all literals generated from RDF triples.
        Parameters:
        rdfModel - a Model of an RDF document, containing triple statements that will be converter to facts.
        Returns:
        a set of literals corresponding to the statements of given rdfModel.
